Class AttributeRuleDetails

java.lang.Object
  com.serena.dmclient.objects.AttributeRuleDetails
All Implemented Interfaces:
DimensionsObjectDetails
public class AttributeRuleDetails
extends java.lang.Object
implements DimensionsObjectDetails

Represents the details of a Dimensions attribute rule. A rule specifies the following:

  1. The role a user must have. Optional: the state the object must have, in order to allow or disallow updates to the attribute.
  2. Whether an attribute should be displayed as part of the role section given by a user role.
  3. Whether an attribute must have a value before the object can be actioned to a new state.

Constructor Detail

AttributeRuleDetails

public AttributeRuleDetails()
Constructs an uninitialized attribute rule object.

AttributeRuleDetails

public AttributeRuleDetails(java.lang.String attributeName,
                            java.lang.String userRole)
Constructs an attribute rule object for the specified attribute and user role. The constructed attribute rule will indicate that:
  • The attribute should be displayed as part of the role section given by the role.
  • The attribute can be updated at any lifecycle state.
  • The attribute might not have a value before the object is actioned to a new state.

Parameters:
attributeName - the attribute name.
userRole - the user role name.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if either attributeName or userRole is null.

AttributeRuleDetails

public AttributeRuleDetails(java.lang.String attributeName,
                            java.lang.String userRole,
                            java.lang.String currentStatus)
Constructs an attribute rule object for the specified attribute, user role, and current status. The constructed attribute rule will indicate that:
  • The attribute should be displayed as part of the role section given by the role.
  • The attribute can be updated at the specified lifecycle state.
  • The attribute might not have a value before the object is actioned to a new state.

Parameters:
attributeName - the attribute name.
userRole - the user role name.
currentStatus - the current status. This parameter indicates what state the object must have in order to allow or disallow updates to the attribute. Null means any lifecycle state.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if either attributeName or userRole is null.
